indicator.description:
1.Notification rate of new ss+ TB cases: New smear positive TB, cases notified to the National Health authorities   during a specified period  per 100 000 population;

2.Treatment success rate: new smear positive TB cases; new smear positive TB cases successfully treated ( cured plus completed) among new smear positive TB cases notified;

3.Notification rate of all forms of TB cases: TB cases (all forms) notified to the national health authorities during a specified period per 100 000 population.

4.Treatment success rate, laboratory confirmed  New MDR-TB cases: laboratory confirmed new MDR TB cases successfully treated ( cured plus completed)  among those enrolled in second-line treatment during  the year of assessment

target.comment:
1.Notification rate of SS+ forms of TB cases: 29 cases per 100,000 population;
2. Treatment success rate of new SS+ forms: 80%, to be reported by 14 August 2015;
3. Notification rate of all forms of TB cases: 85 cases per 100,000 population;
4.Treatment success rate of MDR-TB cases: 70%, to be reported by 14 November 2015.

actual.comment:
1. Notification rate of new smear positive TB cases: 48.6 (These data were not provided by the MoH despite numerous requests from UNDP);
2. Treatment success rate: new smear positive TB cases for 2012 cohort -81%;
3. Notification rate of all forms of TB cases: N/A (The actual rate is for civil sector only whereas the target was estimated for civil and penitentiary sectors);
4. Treatment success rate of MDR-TB cases: 70% (To be available in 2017, this indicator is analyzed after 36 months from the treatment start).

target.comment:
1. Notification rate of SS+ forms of TB cases: 29 cases per 100,000 population;
2. Treatment success rate of new SS+ forms: 81%, 2013 cohort;
3. Notification rate of all forms of TB cases: 85 cases per 100,000 population;
4. Treatment success rate of MDR-TB cases: 80%.

